        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 5:13AM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 513 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Broadview, or 25 miles north of Clovis, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Grady, Broadview and Bellview.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
